(b)} and has already been computed. Take the derivative of that
function:

\begin{align*}
f'(x) &= \frac{6}{5}x^{-4/5} + \frac{6}{5}x^{1/5} \\
&= \frac{6(x+1)}{5x^{4/5}}\end{align*}
